##On Earth I spent 10 hours in the ICU of Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital

Micro-signal Zairenjian11

Features, with a calm narrative against the cold | phoenix network produced in the human studio

Phoenix News Client, produced by Phoenix Network Studio on Earth

Open the Phoenix News client, search "on earth" and follow

One

February 8 Lantern Festival. After 9:00 pm, the old people and children are already asleep. My wife and I are up, watching the news on our phones. Suddenly, a message appeared in the work group. The director said, "Beijing Wuhan Video Emergency Support, involving the hospital connection, with Tan Zhiliang in charge of connecting the whole set of protective equipment. " Then, the group sent out a video guide wearing off protective clothing.

I was startled when I suddenly felt a sense of tension. But on second thought, Wuhan so many people, not necessarily will find me.

My name is Li Shun, in Huawei work, based in Wuhan, service operators communications business, is to ensure that your mobile phone network communications can make calls, can access the Internet. This year due to the closure of the city of Wuhan, many field colleagues can not go back, stay in Wuhan Chinese New Year about 100 people.

But then the director called me. Because it's a special situation, and it's an epidemic area, and people want to go, but they don't have to. I had a brief understanding of the mission information, although more tangled, but think about it, or reply, "I will stand by, ready to go out. ".

Hung up the phone, my wife next to me also froze, eyes fixed on me. I hastened to comfort her, "work needs" . We do communications support, often there will be some urgent tasks, such as the network failure here, then you have to go to the scene to solve the problem. My wife and I quickly agreed that after this mission, I would isolate myself.

Unexpectedly, that night was about to leave.

The mission involves five hospitals in Wuhan, with the exception of the East Lake Hotel, the Wuhan Union Hospital, the Huoshenshan Hospital, the Jinyintan Hospital, and the Wuzhan's shelter hospital, all of which are places to receive new coronavirus pneumonia patients. We need to install equipment to connect five locations in Wuhan to a video conference in Beijing.

The online video conferencing system, Huawei Cloud WeLink, uses a camera and a 65 inch smart screen to allow for more real time and clarity in remote consultations.

We knew where we were going, we didn't know where, but we got it quickly. According to the station, I was assigned to Golden Pond Hospital. "Bad luck, " I thought to myself, a bit self-deprecating.

As Wuhan people, we all know that the Golden Pool Hospital usually only treats infectious patients, other diseases do not see. This time, it only treated new patients with pneumonia, and are critically ill patients.

I didn't tell my wife which hospital I was going to, and she still doesn't know.

After I answer the phone, I wait for the company car to come and pick me up. At 12 o'clock at night, we went to the company to get protective equipment, protective clothing is a up and down one-piece clothes, wear is relatively simple, is to try to seal up their own. We worked in teams of two, one of US pulling the strings, the other putting together the equipment for the live video link.

■ Li Shun donned protective clothing downstairs at Huawei's Hubei Representative Office.

It was nearly two o'clock in the morning when we got to Golden Pond Hospital. On the way, we contacted the hospital. The hospital said that the TV should be put into the nurses'station in the ICU ward. At that time, we heard that the ICU had collapsed again, but there was no way out. The mission had to be accomplished.

Arrived at the hospital entrance, very quiet, gold and Silver Pool Hospital sign is very big, red a few big characters flashing red. We went straight from the service entrance to the ICU on the seventh floor.

We Lug the equipment, including a 65 inch TV screen, into the elevator and then drag it out again. The word "cleaning area" was the word that came into sight. On the other side of the glass door was the ICU ward. I took a picture with my phone.

■ The glass door between the clean and unclean areas.

There are two main areas of the hospital area, clean area and non-clean area, non-clean area is the ICU ward. There's a door in the middle of the hallway between the two sections, and once you're inside, you'll find the ICU ward, where all the nurses are at night. The cleaning area is actually very small. There are several rooms next to the cleaning room. There is also a temporary place, very simple, like a dormitory, where the nurses on duty may rest.

There was no one in the hospital in the early morning. I only saw the security guard and the nurse on duty at the door. No family outside the ICU, just paramedics. It was very quiet.

■ Li Shun's colleagues work in the conference room next to the survey equipment.

The nurse on duty opened the door for us and led us to the cleaning area. We thought we'd try to assemble and debug the equipment in the clean area first, and then move it to the non-clean area, so we could spend less time inside. When we laid out the equipment, the Dean came to coordinate the relevant matters, he also put next to the "Wuhan refueling" four words.

DEBUGGING EQUIPMENT IN ICU nurse Station of Jinyintan Hospital.

From the point of view of homework, it's actually quite simple. But because we were working in the ward, we were under a lot of stress, so we had to double-wear everything, and we had hand sanitizer with us, so we were very careful. There's hand sanitizer hanging all over the compound, and we wash it every now and then. Protective clothing on the body, like a sauna inside, underwear are basically wet sweat, but the outside is cool swish. No calls in the area, cell phones wrapped in plastic.

DEBUGGING EQUIPMENT IN ICU nurse Station of Jinyintan Hospital.

It was about 6 or 7 in the morning, and the equipment was assembled and adjusted. The head nurse picked up two breakfasts for us and we ate them carefully. The day shift nurses are on duty, and they usually have their morning meetings in the clean-up area before they go to work in the ICU. We heard some doctors come in and talk about the patient's treatment plan, which plan to use, and how to administer the medicine.

Shortly before 7:30, we began entering the ICU ward. Before we went in, the head nurse told us to change the mask and the hood again. We just want to pack up and get out of here as soon as possible. Nurse Station is opposite the ward, a ward inside 4,5 beds, surrounded by a variety of equipment, ward doors are sealed.

About noon, we completed the Beijing and Wuhan side of the five-point connection, sound check, adjustment, and then withdrew. There were dozens of people involved in the project, and I was just a small part in it, pushing the whole thing to the ground. It's a team effort.

■ Wuhan is connected to Beijing via a remote video conferencing system.

On the afternoon of February 10, Beijing and Wuhan connected. It is also a teleconsultation system that allows experts in Beijing to teleconsultate critically ill patients at Wuhan Hospital. When I saw this on TV, I thought what I was doing was very meaningful.

Two

Actually, this isn't my first tour of duty during an outbreak. When Wuhan built the two hospitals of Huoshen Mountain and Raytheon Mountain, the communication support was also completed by our support operators.

On the night of January 26, the director called to say that the 5G station at Vulcan Mountain was open for network optimization and told me to go to the Vulcan Mountain site. I went the next morning. The Vulcan Mountain Hospital is due for delivery in 10 days. The sooner you optimize the network, the sooner you can guarantee the operation of the hospital network, which is the responsibility of the correspondent.

The site's up and running, which means Base station is up and running. One base station after another is built is relatively independent, network optimization is to put them together into a network, through testing, optimization, coverage and interference to solve the problem, so that the user experience will be better.

The day we went to the site, it was the 4th or 5th day of the construction of Vulcan Mountain. There was no one on the road. The traffic was smooth. We didn't get there until about 12:00, because we had to pick up a bunch of people, and then we had to go from the city to the suburbs, and then we ran into a checkpoint, and we couldn't get through, and we said we were going to Vulcan Mountain for communications support. Not yet. We need a pass.

We took a detour to Mount Vulcan.

There's a roadblock about a kilometer from here near Mount Vulcan. I can't get in. There were a lot of supply vehicles parked in the middle of the road. We had to get out of the car and walk about 20 minutes to the site. It might have rained for the first few days. The road was muddy and our shoes were useless.

■ A construction photo of Mount Vulcan taken by Li Shun.

Vulcan Mountain is a big construction site with lots of excavators, lots of machines, lots of people. 11:00,12:00 at night. Many people work feverishly, everyone's goal is very clear, is to complete their task as soon as possible, to build the Fire God Mountain Hospital.

There were three base stations in the area, which is usually pretty quick, but it was a busy time, like when we adjusted an antenna and waited from 1 p.m. to 5 p.m. Because you need a master with a climbing permit to get up there. There were several units in the construction, mobile, Unicom, telecommunications, can only one, to line up, the tower only so small space.

At that time is the main site construction, two days in a row, built after we want to put some of the surrounding network testing and optimization. WE SPLIT UP, reduce the risk of infection, and try to coordinate as many things as one person can on the ground.

We worked from morning till night, eating and drinking all day. We had bought instant noodles and water when we passed the supermarket on the way, but later we found we didn't need any. There's a lot to connect on the ground.

And unlike the usual construction, usually do not wear a mask, no psychological burden. This time we will deliberately keep a safe distance from everyone and will not touch or sit in some seats at random.

The Fire God mountain site is mainly wearing a mask, no protective clothing, because there is no construction time patients to the site. It's safe, though. The leaders also went to the scene and sent us some protective masks, in case we didn't have enough.

I've been to Mount Vulcan twice, and it started out as a clearing, next to a nursing home, and then dug out the back, levelled the ground and laid out a makeshift ward. The day I went fast, I had already started laying the first waterproof layer, slowly you can see above the building in the Medical Board Room.

Go back to nearly 12 o'clock at night, a classmate sent a message to ask what is wrong? I said it was fine. Why? He said you walked so many steps, only to find that day walked more than 20,000 steps. These days when the city is closed, they walk hundreds of paces in their homes.

Three

Besides these two, I've been on other missions. On February 2nd, for example, a web based assessment test was offered to the Hubei Medical Team Hotel of Shanghai Second Military Medical University to meet their needs for a video conference with the Shanghai Hospital.

Hotel management is very strict. There is a washbasin on the door, there is disinfectant, your shoes first step into the washbasin inside the shoes disinfection, after entering the whole body spray disinfection, and then ear temperature. Your mask on the outside should be replaced with one on the inside. The elevator is divided into two categories, one is for internal use, the use of sterilized personnel, and the other is for external use. Each person had a room, and they hung out their daily laundry in the hallway, disinfected it, and replaced it with clothes to rest.

I've been talking to some of my colleagues. Some of them are in the shelter hospital, where patients are often mild or suspected, and it is dangerous for them to spend so much time in such a large space.

Comparatively speaking, it was the mission at Golden Pool Hospital that impressed me the most. After that, I bought some instant noodles on the way and went to live alone in another house in the community.

The old people and children at home do not know that I have been to the Golden Pool Hospital. The day after I left, my wife explained the situation to them, and they were more supportive of my work. The child is a first-grade, also sensible, tell her this situation, also understand. When I first went to Vulcan Mountain, she cried a lot.

I've been in quarantine for 14 days now, but I'm keeping it in case there's another mission. Breakfast on their own a simple whole day, noon and evening to pick up a meal at home. I called them to leave the food at the door, and I went to get it, but we didn't see each other. We're in the same neighborhood, different buildings. It's easier.

Our community is more serious epidemic, so far more than 80 cases have been confirmed. This is an old community more than a decade away from the source of the incident South China Seafood Market is also 1 km, two crossroads. Every summer we go to the south China seafood market to buy crabs to eat, game we do not touch. To be honest, the game is Unorthodox. There's a lot of people, a lot of traffic, a lot of vehicles stopping there to deliver and unload. Plus, it's right next to the Hankou Railway Station, so there's a lot of traffic, so there's a lot of traffic every morning.

I used to walk past it every day on my way to work. On the 10th, when I saw the whole south China seafood market was closed down, I still felt that the economic losses were quite large. Because the General New Year period, many people in Wuhan will go shopping.

Now I think about it, I'm scared. Before did not wear a mask, so go out, even if not through the south China Seafood Market, take the subway through the next Wuhan Central Hospital. It was the closest hospital to the South China Sea and one of the first to admit the patients.

Four

In previous years, we usually book restaurants for Family Reunion Dinner, and the elders book meals months in advance. The first to the sixth day of the holiday, each family visits New Year. This year, none of that's GonNa Happen.

On the 10th of January, my wife used to talk about taking precautions, and she would talk to me about whether we were still out for dinner? Is there a risk? But that was just talk until January 20th, when the news spread from person to person, and more people were wearing masks on the road.

Huawei's Hubei Representative Office began giving masks to everyone who came in, suggesting we change them every morning and afternoon. Years ago, the original company with customers and colleagues to hold dinner activities, 20, we have a colleague after the New Year to transfer the department, would like to send him dinner, but later, New Year's Eve Dinner, representative office internal dinner, Customer Dinner, are canceled.

Around the 20th, my wife purchased two boxes of N95 masks, a total of 100, less than 200 yuan. I thought it was a waste. Did you need all this? Then the outbreak got so bad, we thought 100 might not be enough, went to the drugstore on the first morning of our vacation to buy masks, found one for 50 yuan, and started to limit purchases to 20 per person.

In the afternoon, we drove to the supermarket to stock up on some food. There wasn't much left, so I bought some fast food, instant noodles, frozen food and fruit. I just thought I'd be out of the House for a couple of days, but I didn't think it would be that big a deal. Some time ago we can wear a mask to go out, to the community downstairs supermarket shopping, the first two weeks of the overall policy tightening, the last week is the community can not go out.

If you can't go out, it's a groupon. Some of our owners set up a temporary group, we buy vegetables in groups. Every day, the delivery man delivers food to the gate of the community. They'd tell us when to come down for dinner, and we'd go down and line up, one at a time, more than a meter apart.

And the groupons are fading. For the past week, supermarkets have been closed to individuals to avoid crowds. You won't be able to buy anything at the supermarket.

Our community regularly disinfection, basically upstairs in the corridor, the elevator inside, including the elevator button will take 84 to disinfection. The entire Wuhan is on a grid search. Every household is required to report their temperature. I have a warm gun at home. This was left by a child when he was very young.

Each building has a two-dimensional code, after scanning the building cluster, building cluster according to grid statistics corridor residents, such as how many calculate a few grid, and then report the relevant situation.

■ Life photos of Li Shun.

I am from Wuhan. I have lived and worked in Wuhan for several decades. Although I have been to Shenzhen for a while, I was mainly in Wuhan. We all like Wuhan very much. Wuhan is the Port Culture, the East, west, south and north of the confluence of the Two Rivers, all-encompassing, people are relatively straight, relatively hot, do not like the corner son.

Wuhan is very big, divided into the Yangtze River and the Han River River. We live in Hankou and probably don't go to the other side of the river all year round. In recent years, digging the subway, the whole public transport is much better, after the subway, the overall travel is much more convenient. It used to take me to Wuchang. I remember when I was a kid, it took me two hours to get there by bus from downtown. Now it takes me maybe an hour to get there from Tianhe Airport by subway.

Outside the colleagues have resumed work, I heard that many places outside Hubei Business District has been opened. I Miss Breakfast in Wuhan, too. Wuhan breakfast not only hot and dry noodles, but also Tofu, fried dough sticks, bean skin. I used to work in the general will eat breakfast outside, the neighborhood next to a lot of such shops. Nothing's open right now.

The outbreak will pass. After that, I want to have a good meal, take my family to the park, take a tour of the green.

Recently, the temperature seems to rise, the temperature is the most comfortable, and not hot, basking in the sun is good.

Now, when I saw the report on TV about the Golden Pool Hospital, I felt so familiar. I can't tell you how hard it was that night.

The sooner you optimize the network, the sooner you can guarantee the operation of the hospital network, which is the responsibility of the correspondent.

The site's up and running, which means Base station is up and running. One base station after another is built is relatively independent, network optimization is to put them together into a network, through testing, optimization, coverage and interference to solve the problem, so that the user experience will be better.

The day we went to the site, it was the 4th or 5th day of the construction of Vulcan Mountain. There was no one on the road. The traffic was smooth. We didn't get there until about 12:00, because we had to pick up a bunch of people, and then we had to go from the city to the suburbs, and then we ran into a checkpoint, and we couldn't get through, and we said we were going to Vulcan Mountain for communications support. Not yet. We need a pass.

We took a detour to Mount Vulcan.

There's a roadblock about a kilometer from here near Mount Vulcan. I can't get in. There were a lot of supply vehicles parked in the middle of the road. We had to get out of the car and walk about 20 minutes to the site. It might have rained for the first few days. The road was muddy and our shoes were useless.

■ Wuhan is connected to Beijing via a remote video conferencing system.

On the afternoon of February 10, Beijing and Wuhan connected. It is also a teleconsultation system that allows experts in Beijing to teleconsultate critically ill patients at Wuhan Hospital. When I saw this on TV, I thought what I was doing was very meaningful.

Two

Actually, this isn't my first tour of duty during an outbreak. When Wuhan built the two hospitals of Huoshen Mountain and Raytheon Mountain, the communication support was also completed by our support operators.

On the night of January 26, the director called to say that the 5G station at Vulcan Mountain was open for network optimization and told me to go to the Vulcan Mountain site. I went the next morning. The Vulcan Mountain Hospital is due for delivery in 10 days. ![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
■ A construction photo of Mount Vulcan taken by Li Shun.

Vulcan Mountain is a big construction site with lots of excavators, lots of machines, lots of people. 11:00,12:00 at night. Many people work feverishly, everyone's goal is very clear, is to complete their task as soon as possible, to build the Fire God Mountain Hospital.

There were three base stations in the area, which is usually pretty quick, but it was a busy time, like when we adjusted an antenna and waited from 1 p.m. to 5 p.m. Because you need a master with a climbing permit to get up there. There were several units in the construction, mobile, Unicom, telecommunications, can only one, to line up, the tower only so small space.

At that time is the main site construction, two days in a row, built after we want to put some of the surrounding network testing and optimization. WE SPLIT UP, reduce the risk of infection, and try to coordinate as many things as one person can on the ground.

We worked from morning till night, eating and drinking all day. We had bought instant noodles and water when we passed the supermarket on the way, but later we found we didn't need any. There's a lot to connect on the ground.

And unlike the usual construction, usually do not wear a mask, no psychological burden. This time we will deliberately keep a safe distance from everyone and will not touch or sit in some seats at random.

The Fire God mountain site is mainly wearing a mask, no protective clothing, because there is no construction time patients to the site. It's safe, though. The leaders also went to the scene and sent us some protective masks, in case we didn't have enough.

I've been to Mount Vulcan twice, and it started out as a clearing, next to a nursing home, and then dug out the back, levelled the ground and laid out a makeshift ward. The day I went fast, I had already started laying the first waterproof layer, slowly you can see above the building in the Medical Board Room.

Go back to nearly 12 o'clock at night, a classmate sent a message to ask what is wrong? I said it was fine. Why? He said you walked so many steps, only to find that day walked more than 20,000 steps. These days when the city is closed, they walk hundreds of paces in their homes.

Three

Besides these two, I've been on other missions. On February 2nd, for example, a web based assessment test was offered to the Hubei Medical Team Hotel of Shanghai Second Military Medical University to meet their needs for a video conference with the Shanghai Hospital.

Hotel management is very strict. There is a washbasin on the door, there is disinfectant, your shoes first step into the washbasin inside the shoes disinfection, after entering the whole body spray disinfection, and then ear temperature. Your mask on the outside should be replaced with one on the inside. The elevator is divided into two categories, one is for internal use, the use of sterilized personnel, and the other is for external use. Each person had a room, and they hung out their daily laundry in the hallway, disinfected it, and replaced it with clothes to rest.

I've been talking to some of my colleagues. Some of them are in the shelter hospital, where patients are often mild or suspected, and it is dangerous for them to spend so much time in such a large space.

Comparatively speaking, it was the mission at Golden Pool Hospital that impressed me the most. After that, I bought some instant noodles on the way and went to live alone in another house in the community.

The old people and children at home do not know that I have been to the Golden Pool Hospital. The day after I left, my wife explained the situation to them, and they were more supportive of my work. The child is a first-grade, also sensible, tell her this situation, also understand. When I first went to Vulcan Mountain, she cried a lot.

I've been in quarantine for 14 days now, but I'm keeping it in case there's another mission. Breakfast on their own a simple whole day, noon and evening to pick up a meal at home. I called them to leave the food at the door, and I went to get it, but we didn't see each other. We're in the same neighborhood, different buildings. It's easier.

Our community is more serious epidemic, so far more than 80 cases have been confirmed. This is an old community more than a decade away from the source of the incident South China Seafood Market is also 1 km, two crossroads. Every summer we go to the south China seafood market to buy crabs to eat, game we do not touch. To be honest, the game is Unorthodox. There's a lot of people, a lot of traffic, a lot of vehicles stopping there to deliver and unload. Plus, it's right next to the Hankou Railway Station, so there's a lot of traffic, so there's a lot of traffic every morning.

I used to walk past it every day on my way to work. On the 10th, when I saw the whole south China seafood market was closed down, I still felt that the economic losses were quite large. Because the General New Year period, many people in Wuhan will go shopping.

Now I think about it, I'm scared. Before did not wear a mask, so go out, even if not through the south China Seafood Market, take the subway through the next Wuhan Central Hospital. It was the closest hospital to the South China Sea and one of the first to admit the patients.

Four

In previous years, we usually book restaurants for Family Reunion Dinner, and the elders book meals months in advance. The first to the sixth day of the holiday, each family visits New Year. This year, none of that's GonNa Happen.

On the 10th of January, my wife used to talk about taking precautions, and she would talk to me about whether we were still out for dinner? Is there a risk? But that was just talk until January 20th, when the news spread from person to person, and more people were wearing masks on the road.

Huawei's Hubei Representative Office began giving masks to everyone who came in, suggesting we change them every morning and afternoon. Years ago, the original company with customers and colleagues to hold dinner activities, 20, we have a colleague after the New Year to transfer the department, would like to send him dinner, but later, New Year's Eve Dinner, representative office internal dinner, Customer Dinner, are canceled.

Around the 20th, my wife purchased two boxes of N95 masks, a total of 100, less than 200 yuan. I thought it was a waste. Did you need all this? Then the outbreak got so bad, we thought 100 might not be enough, went to the drugstore on the first morning of our vacation to buy masks, found one for 50 yuan, and started to limit purchases to 20 per person.

In the afternoon, we drove to the supermarket to stock up on some food. There wasn't much left, so I bought some fast food, instant noodles, frozen food and fruit. I just thought I'd be out of the House for a couple of days, but I didn't think it would be that big a deal. Some time ago we can wear a mask to go out, to the community downstairs supermarket shopping, the first two weeks of the overall policy tightening, the last week is the community can not go out.

If you can't go out, it's a groupon. Some of our owners set up a temporary group, we buy vegetables in groups. Every day, the delivery man delivers food to the gate of the community. They'd tell us when to come down for dinner, and we'd go down and line up, one at a time, more than a meter apart.

And the groupons are fading. For the past week, supermarkets have been closed to individuals to avoid crowds. You won't be able to buy anything at the supermarket.

Our community regularly disinfection, basically upstairs in the corridor, the elevator inside, including the elevator button will take 84 to disinfection. The entire Wuhan is on a grid search. Every household is required to report their temperature. I have a warm gun at home. This was left by a child when he was very young.

Each building has a two-dimensional code, after scanning the building cluster, building cluster according to grid statistics corridor residents, such as how many calculate a few grid, and then report the relevant situation.

■ Life photos of Li Shun.

I am from Wuhan. I have lived and worked in Wuhan for several decades. Although I have been to Shenzhen for a while, I was mainly in Wuhan. We all like Wuhan very much. Wuhan is the Port Culture, the East, west, south and north of the confluence of the Two Rivers, all-encompassing, people are relatively straight, relatively hot, do not like the corner son.

Wuhan is very big, divided into the Yangtze River and the Han River River. We live in Hankou and probably don't go to the other side of the river all year round. In recent years, digging the subway, the whole public transport is much better, after the subway, the overall travel is much more convenient. It used to take me to Wuchang. I remember when I was a kid, it took me two hours to get there by bus from downtown. Now it takes me maybe an hour to get there from Tianhe Airport by subway.

Outside the colleagues have resumed work, I heard that many places outside Hubei Business District has been opened. I Miss Breakfast in Wuhan, too. Wuhan breakfast not only hot and dry noodles, but also Tofu, fried dough sticks, bean skin. I used to work in the general will eat breakfast outside, the neighborhood next to a lot of such shops. Nothing's open right now.

The outbreak will pass. After that, I want to have a good meal, take my family to the park, take a tour of the green.

Recently, the temperature seems to rise, the temperature is the most comfortable, and not hot, basking in the sun is good.

Now, when I saw the report on TV about the Golden Pool Hospital, I felt so familiar. I can't tell you how hard it was that night.
